#Refund Request

```shell
curl "https://knoxsecure.com/api/v1.1/payment_api/refund"
  -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: API_key:API_Secret" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{ "trans_id":"0000001","amount":"4.99"}'
```

```php
<?php
include KnoxSecure;

$KnoxSecure = new KnoxSecure(API_KEY,API_SECRET);
$data = [
  "trans_id"=>"0000001",
  "amount"=>"4.99"
];

$response = $KnoxSecure->refundPayment($data);

print_r($response);
?>
```

>Expected json resonses:

```json
//Success Response
{
  "trans_id": "00001",
  "amount": "9.28",
  "status": "success"
}
 //Failed Response
{
  "trans_id": "00001",
  "message": "already refunded",
  "amount": "9.28",
  "status": "fail"
}
```

This is the endpoint to setup refunds.

###HTTP Request Information
|Category|Value|
|--------|-----|
|HTTP Request|POST|
|URL|https://knoxsecure.com/api/v1.1/payment_api/refund|

###Parameters
|Parameter|Required|Type|Description|
|---------|--------|----|-----------|
|trans_id|yes|String|Valid Transaction Id|
|amount|yes|Decimal|Amount To Process, Must Match With Order Amount|